race.comment: OFF THE PRESS (8) scored an impressive win when resuming time out here on the course proper over 1000m. Has a strong second-up record and is all set to make it two-for-two this prep. ASTUNNER (9) raced on the speed and kept going to get the job done last time out over this journey at Cootamundra. Peaking now and gets his chance to go back-to-back. KING TAURUS (7) was a determined winner last time at Moruya, scoring by half a length over this distance. Gets some weight relief this time so he is one of the contenders again. GOBBO'S MATE (4) continued the good recent form when he finished just under a length away in third last time out at Jerilderie. Has good early speed so should take up a forward position. Must be respected. MANSIERE (5) doesn't win out of turn but can play a role on peak figures. Inside draw another positive.
